- weren't a separate constituency then. It was Rossshire. I remember the name of one of the candidates. W. Galloway Weir. Yes, I remember that, yes. Then there was another - Stornaway doctor, Doctor McDonald. And then in 1918 - the Western Isles were - We
stern Isles had their own members. The famous Doctor Donald Murray. Yes.
