\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 I - well I don't remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. They wouldn't bother coming out of Stornaway would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
We - we just - they - they used to - they - they used to - to go to - the village. To - to - to the various villages, and - get a - three of four together and explain their views, then they would go to another village. That was
 the - the - the only way they could get people to vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. Much the same as it is now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Yes, that's - that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Could you tell me about Sunday, were your parents Church of Scotland or United Free?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 First of all I remember i
t was Free Church. That was - in 1900 - the Free Church and the United Presbyterians united. And formed the United Free Church. Well - a certain - portion of the older - if I say so, of the old - the Free Church didn't go into - that's the present - Free 
Church we have now. Now, there was - a lot of trouble about that, about the - the property of the church. It even - even went to the House of Lords. Now - Sunday was upset - was ;- well not - not very strictly. But - it was observed here. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 When you say not very strictly what do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Well - once upon a time in the olden days people weren't allowed to - to even to - even to - of course - I remember that myself, we - we weren't allowed to take any water out of - of the well on Sunday, we had
 to take it on the - the Saturday and - and - even a - long ago the - the - it was just a - say - attending to animals or anything like that. Just a - anything that was - out of necessity. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 But you could do the work, looking after the animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Oh - well - well - of course we could, because there were so many animals here that had to be looked after. Now - now - now - as an ordinary crofter for - one or two cows, see that was different. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did you go to church yourself as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Not just to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, no. To - when I remember first there used to be a horse and - cart over here. It used to take five or six people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And both your mother and father would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Would the people from the farmhouse, the servants, would they come too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Yes. But - the - the - well they - they used to take the - the girls, because - the - the - the distance was - was rather - dis - was rather - 
long for a - for a - a lady to - it meant up to five miles. But a - a strapping young fellow of twenty or twenty-one could easily make it. Yes. Yes. I remember the first motor car that came to Lewis.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 That was in the 1920's was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, no, no, no, long - long - long before - yes, long before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Whose car was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And - I remember the - the penny-farthing motor - the penny-farthing push - push bike. Yes, I remember that quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Who had the motor cars that came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 It was
 a - a - a fishing tenant at Morsgail. Morsgail Lodge. I remember it well. He had something to do - he had - he had some - something to do with - the - the old established Church of Scotland. He was - what they call the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10364004\charrsid11559355 genitor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 , like trustees. Well, he use
d to come - once or twice a season to - to visit - the parish ministers who happened at the time to be a very old man, and - the motor car was an old Albion, you could hear it - the noise of it - five miles away. Yes. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 You were in school were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, the - the - the schoolmaster allowed us to - you could hear that - coming up the - the Glen, the - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 It was probably before 1912 then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh - that would be about 19 - 06 or 07. When the - the - the schoolmaster allowed us to 
- to - to stand at the window to see it - passing along, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 They were English people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Well they - they - they were both - shoot - shooting and fishing there, they had the - the - the let of it for - for the season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 They wouldn't mix much with the people round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, but - but that - at - to his Lodge here, right opposite where you stay. That was another shooting and fishing place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Who were the people there when you were a boy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 The first Lord Belper. Now that would be the - that would be the grand - is there a Lord Belper today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 I've never heard of one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Oh didn't you. Oh. Well - the - the second Lord Belper, he was a - he was - Algernon Strutt, and he ceded - he succeeded to the title - title
 when his father died. Yes, now - his daughter - was - now who - is it the Duke of Norfolk, yes, his daughter is married to the Duke of Norfolk. Yes. Now I don't - not really sure if there is a - if there is a - a Lord Belper now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did they have sort of big shootings parties at Vig Lodge as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Well - in those days - this - this young Belper - I think he was a Major in the army, and - especially in - in autumn when - when there used to be deer shooting, they used to have - they'd have six or sev
en - off - officers up 1 up with him. And then - after the first war - Major Digby from Dorsetshire, he was there until he had to - he had to - to leave when the - when - in 1939 when the second war - he was - he was Lord Li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10364004\charrsid11559355 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 utenant of the Country, he - he had to - he had to - to go. But before the was declared. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Would you meet these people when they came? Would they call on you, when you were a boy would they come round to the farm here or would they be very much kept to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, not 
altogether stick to themselves. Because - I remember - every - every - when they came up every year usually - usually about the beginning of July, that was the - the beginning of the fishing - fishing season. Well - they used to - whenever the - whenever 
my father and the - the next farmer over there, they would - oh they would like to meet them, yes, very much so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Would your father go fishing with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No. No, I don't remember my father ever - but - he was going fishing with - but - they us
ed to - to send the salmon up here every season, and - a quarter of venison. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 There were deer in the hills then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Yes, oh yes. Yes, there - I think the - the complement for the season here used to be - eighteen stags. And then - 
so - so many hinds, that - that's the - the female deer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And they would employ people from round here on those hunts as beaters would they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, ghil - ghil - ghillies we call them here. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And to fish, to row the boat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Yes
. OH yes. Yes. Yes. And then - they used to be - one or two in the gardens. And - five or six people employed for - most of the summer, securing the peat supply. So that - that - it - they used to - to - employ quite a lot of people in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 For the farm here you got your own peat supply?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did you share the peat moor with the crofters or did you have your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, it was - it was our own. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Was there any co-operation between the farm and the crofters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh yes. Yes, very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 In what sort of ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
In those days - the - the - crofters - kept more stock than they do nowadays, although the - although - places were poor. A good cow - was - essential to - to a poor family. Now - the - the origin
al crofters here was - three acres and a cow. Three acres of land to one cow. You were - you were supposed to - to raise enough crop out of that to - to keep a cow. Now - the - every - cr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10364004\charrsid11559355 a}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 fting - it's not village we call it here but a township - well they 
had their own regulations to - the stock would have to - to be removed on a certain date, to the - to the outer pastures, for shieling purposes. Now - they used to - the farms here - being - being - basically sheep farms there was a - a lot - of pasture t
h
at - that was - more suitable for - for - for cows to graze upon. With the result that they used to - turn out crofters to graze - where the - the - their stock there were - oh and anything up to two months. Now - they used to - to pay that in labour. Per
haps some of us had a day sheep shearing. Perhaps sheep dipping. Yes.
