de. But then - you know the - the - you know - they call them - you know these - these rigs, some people call them lazy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10364004\charrsid11559355  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
birds, yes, well - well you - you couldn't plough that with a - with a big swing plough with a pair of horses. But then - as far - a sma
ll wooden American plough came on the scene. And one - one little horse could plough it. So that was the answer. Yes, you could - it - it was liked.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And that was lent out was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh - a - a - a lot of crofters got - possessed - got ploughs themselves, yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Can you tell me about the village, who would be the most important people in this part, would the minister be the most important person?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Well - the minister would be the most important person in the parish. Because
 the - the minister was - wasn't - living in the village. No, he was - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 I thought there was a Manse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, but - the - the nearest religious crowd was a half a mile away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Across the Sound?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Across the Sound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 You walk across the sand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Yes, and - and - every - ever township has it's own, as - we have still, it's own grazing committee. These were peop - people elected for - for three years. I think it used to be five once upon a time, to - that was to enforce the grazing regul
ations and to keep order. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 So the leaders of the village would be crofters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh yes. Yes, yes. Any - any other person wasn't - wasn't - elected for - to - to be nominated as a - as a member of the grazing committee.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Were you brought up t
o think of all people as being really sort of equal or were you brought up to feel that some were superior to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 That - that we were - we were taught - to respect - old people. Older than ourselves, especially - especially old - old people. Ol
d men and old ladies. Yes. And we did that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 So that the most important division was one of age rather than of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Well - well - as for occupation, there was - there was the - the minister. And the schoolmaster. Well these - the
se would be the important persons. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And the gamekeeper at the Lodge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh he was - he was a - a person with authority. Yes, oh yes. Yes. And - people respected the farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Your father was very much on a level with those people was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, because of - the farmers were - good to them, the people respected - that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And people who were good workers were respected weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Who provided well for their families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And people who were widely travelled, old soldiers, they were respected.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Yes. I remember - I remember quite well - when - quite a - quite a number of - some of them are still living - who - who fought in the South African war. Yes. They - they had tales}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10364004\charrsid11559355 
 to tell. Oh yes. Yes. Foot - f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 oot slogging right across - the - the African veldt and all that sort of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 When you were a boy did you feel that the crofters were sort of poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, I wouldn't say that they were poor people. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 You felt that the children of the crofters were very similar to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh yes. Yes, we were in the - in the same school and the same class. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 You didn't feel distinctions there in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, no, no, no. Class distinction? No. No. Not even the - the - the schoolmaster's child - children. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Would your parents allow you to play with whatever children you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Were you brought up to give to the poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Oh yes. Yes. Because - in those days - I wouldn't altogether say poor. But there would be the - the occasionally - needy case. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Would your family help them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Yes. My father and mother would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 How would they help, would they give them meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, or - or - sometimes - c
lothing, that was - that was before the - the - the old age pensions, but that - that changed - the - the face of the whole - countryside, yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Can you tell me what sort of games you would play as a boy? If you had any time for games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Well - well - all the games we used to play was at school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 What sort of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Tug o' war. Yes, and - what we called - rounders. And - shinty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs M. It's a ball game played with sticks.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs M. The girls had bohacks.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Didn't they?</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. Playing house - houses, you know, children always do play houses.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 You call that bohacks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. Bohacks, ye
s, yes. I've heard - that he as the youngest of the family had a lot of new fangled toys to try that the others didn't have.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs M. What was that toy you got once that nobody .....</subject3>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 The - first of all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs M. You had tops didn't you?</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Yes, we - we - my - my father used to make that for us. And we used to - to make them ourself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. And what about stilts, didn't you walk - didn't you have stilts?</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Oh yes, get - get across the fords with them. Yes. But - the - the first toy that I can remember - well it wasn't a toy, a mouth organ. And then the - the Newish Harp. Yes. Then - then - toys - then - I got the - the fright of my life in the false
 face I saw. False face. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. Didn't you have a monkey on a stick or something? What toy did you have?</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 There weren't any sort of clubs for boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 All your amusements were made by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, not that I can - not that I can remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 You say that you played these musical instruments yourself, did anyone else in the family play a musical instrument?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, of course - of course I got - I got my mouth organ - would - would be quite enough for a - for a whole family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 There was a piano was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 It's been in the family ever since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Is that from your mother's side or your father's side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 It was at the farm. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Who would play that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
What? I don't really know if - any of the boys could - could play it. I think it was more of an ornament, because - in those days, you - a young - a strapping young boy as we were - we hadn't the time. No - no 
sir, we had to be - to be en - engaged otherwise. Yes. There was always - always so much to be done. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Was there anyone who sang in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 What? No, not - I don't think so. They used to - to - do the best we could in church. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 You weren't in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did anything special happen on a birthday as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, we - we used to get - presents. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Would you have some friends to a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh no, no, not to - not to that extent. No. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Were there no occasions when you had a children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10766441\charrsid11559355 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 s party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No - on the - all the activities we had were connected with the school. Yes. We used to have - a New Year party. And - we used to - the L}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10766441\charrsid11559355 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 eutenant in the Lodge there used to 
entertain the - the children every year, we used to play games. That was a - a gala day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did you ever go away from here on a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 I - I couldn't say that I went on a holiday. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10766441\charrsid11559355 You mean you went }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 on a kind of working holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Well - more - more or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Where would that be to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Well, I - I used to - to go to Inverness more or less on business but it - a combination of both.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 That was after you left school though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh - no - since the last - decade I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 I meant when you were a child you never went on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. But his father used to drive cattle to the mainland, even as far as Falkirk.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did he really? He drove cattle all the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Well - not - not - not to - not from Lewis. From - from the mainland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 But while he was here would he drive them to Stornaway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No - well - yes. Yes, yes, many - many a - many a time I - I was on that job myself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 How long did that take you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Usually three days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And you'd sleep in peoples houses on the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Oh yes. Oh yes. There was a - a - the markets - where - very well arranged then. There was a market half way between this - between Uig and Stornaway a cattle market. Ov
er at Garynahine. Yes. Now that would serve a - what we call the west side. Then - the main market was at Stornaway. And - we - we used to - to send the - the cattle to the - to the mainland, to the - auction - market on the mainland. Dingwall. Sometimes 
Inverness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And your mother used to sew your father's money in a belt round his body didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
I don't think that - I believe it was my grandmother that used to do that. But - but I - I remember my father have - having the shepherds plaid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. That's the black and white - shepherds tartan.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Mr. F. Yes. Yes. Yes. That was his - that was his - his - his - covering from the rain, which was very good, yes, because - you could - you could - fold it over your head. It was - tied on with - cross straps. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Would you say that your parents had close friends around here, would their particular friends be other farmers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Well - the way - the way of things - that this particular - this particular farm here - it w
as more a - more or less a kind of half way house, people from the - the villages up there, when they used to on - on foot - perhaps right down to - to Miarig, well - they used to stop in here for a rest, and for a meal. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Would they be invited or would they just call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No, that was - that was the - the custom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. They used to keep a light burning in the window of this house to guide travellers.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mr. F. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. Across the sand.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mr. F. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Across the sands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Yes, the front of the house looks onto the sands and it's - the sand were the right of way weren't they, there were no roads. Short cuts when the tide was out, you can cut off miles by crossing the sand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mr. F. Oh yes. Oh it - it was a short cut. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Can you tell me when you left school did you stay on and work here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 On the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 On the farm. Then - I was working in the farm here. Then - I went to Glasgow. During the first - world w
ar. I was working on munitions. For William Beard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 That's a famous place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Do you remember all the disputes there, it was before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Before then. Yes. Oh the - Lloyd George was on - the - the king at that time. Yes. Oh yes. If -
 if you remember - we nearly lost the war owing to - to lack of munitions. Then Lloyd George took over, and - what was the name of that other - Lord Beaverbrook, he came along and Winston Churchill was on the same. And - I remember - well - well I remembe
r the day that Lord Kitchener was round. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 You were a Lloyd George man yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 That was the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 How long were you here in Glasgow then, just for the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Not - I - I had a set back, I had a kind of rheumatic fever, I had to come ho
me here. Yes. And before I was fully recovered. I was then - it was military service, but the - there was - I was classified as unfit at the time, and so I was. Well - the war - before I was fit the war - ended. Then - I was - I was working - between the 
farm here and - Uig Lodge. I was doing a lot there, and right on to the - to the last war. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Then the crofts were broken up and you took one of the crofts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 When would your father have died then, after the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 My father died in 1932.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 He'd retired by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes, yes. Died then at the age - age of eighty-six. Mrs. M. It was a terrible ordeal for them when the farms were broken up, they lost their liv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12806111\charrsid11559355 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 lihood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 How did they manage after that, did they just retire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. Yes I suppose so.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12806111\charrsid11559355 Mrs. F. Who}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 ?</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. When the farms broke up - when the farm was broken up your father had retired by then more or less?</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mr. F. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. But the - this croft was in his name at first.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Mr. F. Yes, being the - the - the - the proprietor - he had - he had a kind of a priority. The estate workers - had the - they were - they were supposed to get - to get a croft. Because
 their - their service would be ended, would be finished then. And - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Can you tell me what's happened to the other members of your family your brothers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes, indeed. One of them was in Australia died last year. Another -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 What did he do in Australia?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Well - he was at various jobs. He was first of all - he was - down at Cardiff, he served his apprenticeship - as a - to the drapery trade. And then he emigrated in 1910 to Australia, there was a great hue and cry for men for the Colonies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. And didn't you have parties before members of the fam - when members of the family emigrated, farewell parties.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mr. F. Oh yes. Yes. Yes, although there were - all but - all friends - all relatives, yes. Then - the next on
e - went to South America in 1906. And then the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 What did he do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
Farming. Ranching. Yes. And then - one who is with us here - went to the - United States 1910. He only came back here but he had retired two or three years - three or four - sixty-six, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 What was he doing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Sheep farming, yes. They call it there ranching. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 One brother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And then there's the sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Yes. One of them - she's still living. She - she was a nurse. Spent her lif
e in London. That's where she still is. Yes. She trained in Glasgow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 And the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Oh well, the other was mostly at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Did she marry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197677 KF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 No. Being the - the youngest - it was the same with me, we had to - all the other were away
, we had to - stay at home to look after our parents - after our parents. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 What about your wife's brothers, have they left the island?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. They all went to Canada.</subject3>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Farming again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14184279 K3  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 Mrs. M. No. They - they didn't have a farming background. My elder uncle was a fisherman, a fine fisherman. And the younger one became a 
\{BLANK\} refrigeration expert.</subject3>}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid9644372\charrsid11559355 
\par }}